It’s never making future plans because you never know when your next cycle will be. 
It’s missing out on trips & gatherings because of clinic visits. 
It’s putting all of your savings towards treatments.
It’s feeling lonely when nobody understands what you’re going through. 
It’s feeling devastated when it ends in loss.
It’s feeling excited to start all over again.
-
The fertility world is a complicated one and it’s hard to feel like you’re doing it when you’re in the thick of it. Our story isn’t over though, I know it. If you’re in this season - I see you.

It’s my mom’s birthday today! 🥳🤍 Happy birthday to the best mom, friend & nanny in the world! We love you and we hope you have a great day! Can’t wait to celebrate you 🫶🏼!

Last month sucked (as a nice way to put it 🤣). After we found out that we lost our baby, I was struggling big time 💔. So when I started healing physically, I decided to embark on a 21 day movement challenge. I didn’t put any real expectations on myself, I just knew that I needed it. And boy did I need it.
-
I finished my last class a few days ago, and I am still amazed at the changes in my body from the short amount of time. The classes that felt hard in the beginning felt like a breeze at the end and I am feeling SO much stronger 💪🏼!
-
The reality is - it’s hard to find the time to move during our busy days. But I’m so glad I made it a priority. And the days when I got to share my practice with Rosie were my favorite 🤍 (swipe to see our little yogi in the making).
-
It’s funny how things come full circle because when I started yoga years ago, it was during a time when I was really struggling. I like to think it saved me in a way. Fast forward to today: it’s back and it’s grounding me, helping me & healing me 🫶🏼.
-
So here’s to brighter days, and a lot more downward dogs 😉. I’ve already started another monthlong series today! Let’s see where March takes us, shall we?
.
.
.
.
.
.

Our first family vacation and Rosie’s first time using her passport was a success!! 🥰 We took a spontaneous drive to Maine this weekend and I’m so glad we did.
-
We may have spent too much, and ate too much.. but we also laughed so much and had the best time together 🫶🏼. It honestly was just what we all needed.
-
Last night at our last hotel stop, we asked Rosie what her favorite part of the trip was and she said, “just playing with Mimi and mama” 🥹🤍.
-
A few highlights:
🚗 Rosie being the best little traveller
🛒 Allllll of the @target stops
🍺 Good beer and pizza at @mainebeerco
🐠 Driving to Boston and hitting up the @newenglandaquarium and exploring the city
🍝 Rosie’s first time eating dinner at a bar (Olive Garden was SO busy but it was so worth it 🤤)
🍦 And of course all of the yummy treats along the way!
-
People always told us travelling with kids would be hard.. but turns out it’s just whatever you make of it! Can’t wait for our next adventures ☀️!

It’s National Infertility Awareness week. This past year we have been heavy in the fertility world 😵‍💫. I know I’ve been sharing our journey, but here is a *little* glimpse into it all starting from the very beginning:
-
⋒ three failed at home inseminations
⋒ two failed non-medicated iuis 
⋒ seven failed medicated iuis 
⋒ hsg & hssg scans
⋒ 1 miracle baby
⋒ the toll on our mental health
⋒ 3 failed medicated iuis (round 2)
⋒ 1 egg retrieval
⋒ 1 frozen embryo transfer
⋒ thousands of dollars paid out of pocket
⋒ a missed miscarriage
-
Sending love to everyone who needs it 🧡. This journey is no joke but I’m proud of us and wouldn’t change a thing.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

It’s finally happening and we can’t keep it a secret any longer.. WE’RE PREGNANT! 👶🏼 Our sweet rainbow baby is due to join us in December 🌈🥹!! We are completely over the moon and are already counting down the days until we get to meet our baby.
-
Pregnancy after loss is hard and I would be lying if I said I still don’t worry that something could go wrong. But ultimately, we are done living in fear and are ready to celebrate and share the news of our tiny miracle! I still can’t believe that we will soon be a family of four AND that Rosie will be a big sister 😭!!
-
So stay tuned! We have so much to share and I am so excited to watch how this next chapter of ours will unfold 🥰!
-
I also just want to mention that I know how triggering it can be to see pregnancy announcements and am sending extra love to anyone who needs it today 🤍.
.

.

On March 27, 2023 we had our second embryo transfer and it was the best day 🤍 I thought we would be really nervous after our previous loss but to our surprise we were both excited and hopeful! One beautiful embryo was transferred and we were ready for it to stick and get cozy 🥚!
-
To our surprise, we got a faint positive 4 days later, and our tests continued to darken each day. We remained pretty guarded just because things were happening pretty similar to our previous transfer so we were basically holding our breath until our first ultrasound. And well, I guess you know what happened next! There WAS a baby and a heartbeat and it has continued to grow since 🥹👶🏼!
-
We love you already baby 💛!

October is pregnancy and infant loss awareness month and I couldn’t let the month go by without acknowledging our own journey through darker times 🧡. Back in January we transferred a beautiful embaby and got a positive only 5 days later. We started planning and imagining what our lives would look like 9 months down the road but unfortunately at our 7w ultrasound, the doctor put her hand on my knee and said the two words nobody wants to hear at a scan, “I’m sorry”. We were having a missed miscarriage. Our baby had stopped growing but my body didn’t recognize it, so thought it was still pregnant. To say we were devastated would be an understatement 💔.
-
Society tells us pregnancy shouldn’t be shared before 12 weeks, but I think that’s stupid. The excitement you have for your baby at 5,6,7 or 8 weeks should matter just as much as after 12 weeks. 1 in 4 pregnancies end in miscarriage. We felt alone, but I know we weren’t. Early pregnancy loss is still a loss.
-
We should have welcomed this baby into the world back in September, but instead we’re pregnant with our rainbow baby. And while I am SO grateful for this current pregnancy, I’ll always still wonder about the little bean we lost 🌈✨. Sending love to everyone who needs it this month - whether you’ve shared your story or not, your baby mattered 🧡.
-

It’s hard to put into words how the last week unfolded for us, but because I’ve always been so transparent about our fertility & pregnancy journey, I will continue to share incase it could ever help someone else going through something similar ❤️.
-
Charlie was born December 1st with no issues and we were actually discharged the following day. However, 5 days later I took a turn and started bleeding and passing large clots. My gut told me something was wrong, so we headed in to be checked and I’m so glad we did. I was rushed into surgery that evening and ended up having quite a serious postpartum hemorrhage that led to multiple blood transfusions and a 6 day hospital stay ❤️‍🩹.
-
To say this is not how I imagined my first week postpartum would be an understatement and I am honestly still trying to process everything that has happened. Thankfully I am now home, but it definitely is going to take time to heal both physically and mentally from everything that I’ve experienced.
-
I am extremely grateful for the exceptional care I received by all of the doctors and nurses during my stay (especially from my living guardian angel @paulettegallanthotmailcom 🥹), the support of our family who stepped up and dropped everything to help with Rosie, and of course my number one - Jess 🧡. She never left my side once, advocated for me when I couldn’t myself, and all while taking care of Charlie and staying strong for our family. 
-
Christmas might not be the picture perfect season that I had envisioned this year by doing all the things and taking in all the activities.. but it sure as hell beats the alternative. So here’s my reminder to anyone navigating those first few days postpartum… if you feel like something is off, go get checked. Birth is so empowering and beautiful but it can also be complicated and scary 🫶🏼.
-
Feels like I have a lot of catching up to do around here.. but happy to report that the Charlie & Rosie picture spam is set to resume shortly 😉❤️🙏🏼.
